[WASHINGTON] Facebook said on Tuesday users had trouble accessing the social network and its other applications such as Instagram for a chunk of the day due to a server software problem.It was the second instance in the past two weeks in which technical issues appeared to affect access to Facebook."Earlier today, a server configuration caused intermittent problems across all apps globally, creating a degraded experience for users," a Facebook spokesman told AFP."The issue has since been resolved, we are back to 100 per cent for everyone, and we're sorry for any inconvenience."The independent monitoring site Downdetector showed a map indicating that outages affected most parts of the world, especially in North America, Europe and Asia.


